// text_scan.su — NTM read head, sequential scan.
// planning/sutra-spec/ram-pointers.md.
//
// Non-halting substrate-RNN: a recurring cursor lives on VRAM and
// advances by one each tick (vector add on the substrate). Each tick it
// is emitted as the pointer the head wants to read. The orchestrator
// (experiments/ntm_ram/orchestrator.py) decodes the pointer, reads the
// host RAM cell, and serves it back as `served` on the next tick. The
// program controls the address sequence on the substrate; the
// orchestrator does the host RAM I/O at the wire. `served` is the
// response slot (unused by a forward scan, consumed by pointer-chasing
// variants).
function vector read_head(vector served) {
    recurring vector cursor = make_real(0.0);
    vector next = cursor + make_real(1.0);
    recur(next);
    return(cursor);
}

function string main() { return "ok"; }
